MultiPixel Community Guidelines
Version 1.0 — Relimintor (Raptor4 / MultiPixel)

These rules apply to:
• All players
• All servers (official and unofficial)
• All Mods
• All community spaces using MultiPixel content

Servers may add additional rules, but may NOT remove or weaken any rule below.

1. RESPECT OTHERS
• No harassment, bullying, or targeted abuse.
• No hate speech or discrimination.
• No threats or intimidation.

2. SAFETY FIRST
• No doxxing or sharing private information.
• No stalking or targeted harassment.
• No encouragement of self-harm or dangerous acts.

3. NO ILLEGAL CONTENT
• No extremist content.
• No terrorist content.
• No illegal political activity.
• No child exploitation or adult content.

4. FAIR PLAY
• No cheating, exploiting, hacking, or automation tools.
• No bypassing anti-cheat or DRM.
• No modified clients or packet manipulation.

5. HONESTY & INTEGRITY
• No impersonating MultiPixel staff, developers, or moderators.
• No claiming official partnership without approval.
• No misleading or fraudulent behavior.

6. SERVER RULES
All servers must:
• Enforce these guidelines.
• Maintain a safe environment.
• Moderate harmful content.
• Follow all MultiPixel licensing rules.

7. DATA & PRIVACY
Servers may collect:
• Join/leave logs
• Chat logs

Servers may NOT collect:
• Personal data
• Payment information
• Sensitive data

8. CONTENT CREATION
Allowed:
• Gameplay videos
• Reviews
• Commentary
• Exposés

Not allowed:
• Reuse of assets outside MultiPixel
• Recreation of assets in similar style

9. CONSEQUENCES
Violations may result in:
• Account bans
• Server bans
• Mod removal
• Revocation of server approval
• Legal action
• Fines or tariffs (for monetization violations)

10. FINAL AUTHORITY
MultiPixel reserves the right to interpret and enforce these guidelines.
